2,4,beat_03_what_changed,"\{STRUCTURE_CH2_ORIGIN_CURRENT_STATE\} \{context_shift_description\} The conditions that made the sentence adaptive \'97 those conditions changed. But the sentence didn't. \{specific_changes[0]\} \{specific_changes[1]\} \{specific_changes[2]\} The world moved. The sentence stayed. What used to keep you safe from \{original_danger\} now keeps you safe from \{current_threat\}. The protection became prevention."\
2,5,beat_04_the_cost,"Here's what the sentence does now: It delays you. \{current_delay_example\} It makes you invisible. \{current_invisibility_example\} Later keeps moving. \{later_keeps_moving_example\} You're not avoiding danger anymore. You're avoiding \{current_avoidance_target\}. And the difference is: \{danger_vs_discomfort_distinction\}"\
2,6,beat_05_why_its_hard_to_let_go,"You've been so loyal to this sentence. It saved you when you were \{origin_age_range\}. It protected you when \{origin_protection_scenario\}. Of course you trust it. But the sentence is still protecting you from \{original_danger_type\} \'97 even though that threat isn't what you're facing anymore. Now you're facing \{current_challenge_type\}. Not \{original_danger_type\}. And the sentence that saved you then is costing you now."\
2,7,beat_06_the_shift,"Here's the shift: Then: \{past_danger_description\} Now: \{present_discomfort_description\} Then: The sentence kept you safe from real risk Now: The sentence keeps you from being visible at all You don't need protection from \{current_situation_type\} the way you needed protection from \{original_situation_type\}. But the sentence doesn't know that. It's still running the same program: wait until it's safer. Except safer never comes."\
2,8,beat_07_what_youre_actually_waiting_for,"You're waiting to feel \{desired_emotional_state\}. But here's what you don't see: \{reality_checks[0]\} \{reality_checks[1]\} \{reality_checks[2]\} The version of you that's \{desired_state\} doesn't exist. Not because you're broken or flawed. Because that's not how being human works."\
