3,1,beat_00_opening,"The sentence shows up everywhere. Not just work. Not just texts. Everywhere. Let me show you where it's been hiding."\
3,2,beat_01_friendship_context,"The friendship that faded. They used to reach out every week. Coffee. A walk. Just checking in. You said maybe. Then maybe again. Then you stopped responding for a while. They didn't get mad. They just... stopped asking. Not because they don't care. Because they learned. The sentence taught them: you're not available. \{core_sentence\} That was the sentence underneath every ""maybe later."""\
3,3,beat_02_creative_context,"The creative thing you used to do. You used to draw. Or write. Or play something. Or make something. It wasn't about being good. It was just something you did. Then one day you didn't. And then another day. And then it had been months. You tell yourself you'll get back to it when you feel inspired again. But inspiration doesn't come first. It never did. The sentence says: What's the point? It won't be any good anyway. So the sketchbook stays closed. The instrument stays in the corner. The thing you used to love stays in the past."\
3,4,beat_03_decision_context,"The decision you keep not making. There's something you need to decide. Maybe it's small. Maybe it's not. You think about it. You almost decide. Then the weight comes. It doesn't matter what I choose. Nothing's going to change. So you don't choose. You wait. You tell yourself you'll decide when you have more clarity. Clarity doesn't come. The decision stays unmade. Life chooses for you."\
3,5,beat_04_body_context,"The body you stopped listening to. You're tired. Or hungry. Or something hurts. You notice it. Somewhere far away, you notice it. But doing something about it would require caring. And caring isn't available. What's the point of eating well? What's the point of rest? What's the point of any of it? So you skip the meal. Or eat something that isn't food. Or stay up too late again. Or don't move for another day. The sentence runs your body now too."\
3,6,beat_05_home_context,"The apartment that looks like this. Dishes in the sink. Clothes on the floor. That thing you meant to fix three months ago. You see it. Every day you see it. You think about doing something. The thought is there. Then the weight. Then the sentence. It's just going to get messy again. Why bother. So it stays. And the staying becomes proof. Proof that you can't handle things. Proof the sentence was right all along."\
3,7,beat_06_family_context,"The version of you that shows up at family things. They ask how you're doing. You say fine. They ask about work. You give the short version. They ask about your life. You change the subject. Not because you're private. Because the real answer is too heavy to carry into a room full of people who expect you to be okay. So you perform okay. And performing takes everything you have. And afterward you're emptier than before. The sentence got you through it: Just get through this. None of it matters anyway."\
3,8,beat_07_future_context,"The thing you keep meaning to do. There's something. You know what it is. Something you've been meaning to start. Or finish. Or try. Every few weeks you think about it. You almost do something. Then: Not today. I don't have it in me today. Today becomes tomorrow. Tomorrow becomes next week. Next week becomes ""someday."" Someday is where the sentence sends everything it doesn't want you to do."\
3,9,beat_08_pattern_recognition,"Here's what you might not have seen: It's the same sentence every time. Different situations. Different stakes. Different people. Same sentence underneath. \{core_sentence\} In your friendships: They don't really care. Why reach out. In your creative life: It won't be good. Why try. In your decisions: It won't change anything. Why choose. In your body: What's the point. Why take care of it. In your home: It'll just get bad again. Why clean. In your family: They won't understand. Why be real. In your future: It's not going to get better. Why start."\
3,10,beat_09_scope_realization,"The sentence isn't one thing you do. It's everything you don't. And here's the part that's hard to see: Each time the sentence wins, it gets stronger. You don't reach out. The friendship fades. You feel more alone. The sentence says: See? No one cares. You don't create. The skill fades. You feel less capable. The sentence says: See? You're not good at anything. You don't decide. Life decides for you. You feel less in control. The sentence says: See? It doesn't matter what you do. The sentence creates the evidence for itself. Every time you listen to it, you prove it right. Not because it's true. Because you stopped testing it."\
3,11,beat_10_operating_system,"This is what the sentence has been doing while you thought you were just tired. Just busy. Just not feeling it. It's been running everything. And the scope of it\'97the everywhere-ness of it\'97that's what you couldn't see until now. It's not one area of your life. It's the operating system."\
3,12,beat_11_beginning,"But here's the thing about seeing it: Once you see it in one place, you start seeing it everywhere. That's not a problem. That's the beginning. \{teacher_voice_reflection_1.text\}"\
4,1,beat_00_opening,"You don't have to stop being \{current_emotional_state\}. That's the first thing you need to know. All this time, you've been trying to solve a problem. You were trying to get rid of being \{current_emotional_state\}. You were trying to make it go away. You were trying to fix it. But here's what you don't see: You were trying to solve the wrong problem."\
4,2,beat_01_the_reframe,"Being \{current_emotional_state\} isn't a malfunction. \{information_system_description\} \{uncertainty_presence_description\} That's it. It's information. Not danger. Not pathology. Information. Your nervous system isn't broken. It's doing exactly what it's supposed to do."\
4,3,beat_02_the_fixing_paradox,"Every time you try to make it go away, here's what actually happens: \{fixing_paradox_explanation\} It makes it worse. Because trying to fix it confirms that it's dangerous. And if it's dangerous, your nervous system sends more of it. The more you fight it, the more your system thinks: This must be serious. Send backup. That's the paradox. The solution became the problem. So what do you do instead? \{letting_it_be_description\} Not because you're giving up. Not because you're resigned. Because it's asking to be noticed, not fixed. You let it be there."\
4,4,beat_03_acting_alongside,"Here's what that actually looks like: \{acting_alongside_scenario.situation\} Before: \{acting_alongside_scenario.before_pattern\} After: \{acting_alongside_scenario.after_pattern\} Same feeling. Different relationship. You stopped needing it to go away before you could \{core_action\}. You can \{core_action\} while \{current_emotional_state\}."\
4,5,beat_04_the_proof_youve_been_ignoring,"And here's the thing you don't realize: You already do this. \{proof_examples[0].context\} \{proof_examples[0].description\} \{proof_examples[1].context\} \{proof_examples[1].description\} \{proof_examples[2].context\} \{proof_examples[2].description\} You've been doing it your entire life. You've just been telling yourself you shouldn't have to."\
