7,2,beat_01_small_move,"A small move is any action you take while the feeling is still there. Not big. Not heroic. Just: doing something anyway. \{small_move_examples[0].context\} Before: \{small_move_examples[0].before\} After: \{small_move_examples[0].after\} \{small_move_examples[1].context\} Before: \{small_move_examples[1].before\} After: \{small_move_examples[1].after\} \{small_move_examples[2].context\} Before: \{small_move_examples[2].before\} After: \{small_move_examples[2].after\} These aren't big. They're not heroic. Small moves build evidence. Not that you're \{desired_state\}. That you can act while not being \{desired_state\}."\
7,3,beat_02_pattern_learning,"Your nervous system learns through repetition. Every time you act while \{current_emotional_state\}, you're teaching it: \{pattern_teaching_description\} Old pattern: \{old_pattern_description\} New pattern: \{new_pattern_description\} That's the shift."\
