moment_1_context: Slack thread, 2pm\
moment_1_situation: 'Someone asks a direct question.\
\
  You know the answer.\
\
  Your fingers hover over the keyboard.\
\
  You look at the screen. The weight settles in.\
\
  What''s the point. It doesn''t matter anyway.\
\
  The thread moves on without you.\
\
  '\
moment_2_context: Team standup, cameras on\
moment_2_situation: 'Your manager asks if anyone has updates.\
\
  You have an update. A decent one.\
\
  Your mouth opens slightly.\
\
  The heaviness. The distance.\
\
  No one cares. It won''t change anything.\
\
  The moment passes. You said nothing.\
\
  '\
moment_3_context: Text draft, 11:47pm\
moment_3_situation: 'There''s a message you should send.\
\
  You look at it. Two sentences.\
\
  You could send it. Your thumb hovers over the button.\
\
  They don''t really want to hear from you.\
\
  You lock your phone. You''ll send it tomorrow. Tomorrow you won''t send it either.\
\
  '\
optional_moment_4_context: Sunday afternoon\
optional_moment_4_situation: 'There''s something you used to enjoy. Something you\
  keep meaning to get back to.\
\
  You think about doing it.\
\
  The thought is there. Then the weight.\
\
  What''s the point. It won''t be any good anyway.\
\
  You don''t do it. You do nothing instead.\
\
  '\
optional_moment_5_context: ''\
optional_moment_5_situation: ''\
cost_example_1_label: The response that's too late\
cost_example_1_detail: 'By the time you send the text, the conversation moved on.\
\
  They don''t respond. Not because they''re upset.\
\
  Because it''s been three days and the moment passed.\
\
  '\
cost_example_2_label: The invite you stopped getting\
cost_example_2_detail: 'They invited you three times.\
\
  You said "maybe" three times. Or nothing at all.\
\
  They stopped asking.\
\
  Not because they don''t like you.\
\
  Because they learned you don''t say yes.\
\
  '\
cost_example_3_label: The version they never see\
cost_example_3_detail: 'The version of you that has things to say\'97that version stays\
  in your head.\
\
  What shows up instead is quieter. Flatter. Less.\
\
  Always waiting. Always the same sentence underneath.\
\
  '\
cost_example_4_label: The idea someone else said\
cost_example_4_detail: 'You thought of it in the first five minutes.\
\
  You waited. You told yourself you''d share it when it mattered.\
\
  Someone else said it 20 minutes later.\
\
  Everyone loved it.\
\
  You sit there knowing you had that first.\
\
  '\
