perceived_virtue_1: being realistic\
perceived_virtue_2: not getting hopes up\
perceived_virtue_3: not wasting energy on things that don't matter\
reality_statement_1: The sentence isn't keeping you safe. It's keeping you frozen.\
reality_statement_2: The sentence isn't describing reality. It's creating it.\
book_promise_statement: 'What if you didn''t have to wait?\
\
  What if the version of you sitting here right now\'97the one who feels nothing, who\
  can''t find the point\'97what if that version is the one who gets to move?\
\
  Not someday. Not when it lifts.\
\
  Now.\
\
  '\
pattern_learning_description: 'So the next time you think about doing something real\'97\
\
  your system says: "Wait. You felt empty last time. That must mean it''s not safe."\
\
  Not because the thing is dangerous.\
\
  But because you taught it that the feeling is the problem.\
\
  '\
origin_age_range: as far back as you can remember\
origin_context: 'There was a time when caring cost too much.\
\
  Maybe it was one thing\'97a loss, a failure, a betrayal that taught you: investing\
  leads to pain.\
\
  Or maybe it was slow. Disappointment stacked on disappointment. Effort that led\
  nowhere. Hope that kept getting crushed.\
\
  '\
origin_specific_situation: 'Until your system learned something:\
\
  Caring hurts. Not caring protects.\
\
  The sentence\'97Nothing matters, so why bother\'97wasn''t random.\
\
  It was a solution.\
\
  Your system found a way to stop the bleeding. If nothing matters, nothing can hurt\
  you. If you don''t try, you can''t fail. If you don''t care, you can''t be disappointed.\
\
  That made sense then.\
\
  '\
origin_outcome: 'The sentence protected you from the pain of disappointment. It kept\
  you safe from caring when caring led to hurt.\
\
  '\
origin_threat: the pain of disappointment, caring when caring led to hurt\
biological_system: nervous system\
time_buying_example: 'The sentence gave you time. Time to not care. Time to not invest.\
  Time to not risk disappointment.\
\
  '\
safety_example: 'It protected you when caring always led to pain. When every investment\
  got punished. When hope was a setup for hurt.\
\
  '\
consequence_avoidance_example: 'You avoided the pain of disappointment. You avoided\
  the hurt of caring. You avoided the risk of investing when investment led nowhere.\
\
  '\
validation_statement: 'The sentence made sense. It was adaptive. It kept you safe.\
\
  Not "it was understandable." Not "you were doing your best."\
\
  It made sense.\
\
  '\
context_shift_description: 'Now you''re here. Still numb. Still waiting.\
\
  The sentence is still running.\
\
  But something shifted. Quietly. Without announcement.\
\
  The conditions that made the sentence adaptive\'97those conditions changed.\
\
  But the sentence didn''t.\
\
  '\
specific_changes:\
- You're not in that situation anymore. The one where caring always led to pain.\
- Where every investment got punished. Where hope was a setup for hurt.\
- The world moved. The sentence stayed.\
