invisible_rule: Nothing matters, so why bother.\
erasure_process_description: 'Each time the sentence wins, it gets stronger.\
\
  You don''t reach out. The friendship fades. You feel more alone. The sentence says:\
  See? No one cares.\
\
  You don''t create. The skill fades. You feel less capable. The sentence says: See?\
  You''re not good at anything.\
\
  You don''t decide. Life decides for you. You feel less in control. The sentence\
  says: See? It doesn''t matter what you do.\
\
  The sentence creates the evidence for itself.\
\
  Every time you listen to it, you prove it right.\
\
  Not because it''s true.\
\
  Because you stopped testing it.\
\
  '\
self_erasure_examples:\
- The friendship that faded because you didn't reach out\
- The creative thing you used to do that stays in the past\
- The decision you keep not making that life chooses for you\
- The body you stopped listening to\
- The apartment that looks like this\
hardest_realization: 'This is what the sentence has been doing while you thought you\
  were just tired. Just busy. Just not feeling it.\
\
  It''s been running everything.\
\
  And the scope of it\'97the everywhere-ness of it\'97that''s what you couldn''t see until\
  now.\
\
  It''s not one area of your life.\
\
  It''s the operating system.\
\
  '\
sentence_protection_claim: 'The sentence told you it was protecting you.\
\
  "Nothing matters, so why bother. Then you''ll be safe."\
\
  But it wasn''t protecting you.\
\
  It was preventing you.\
\
  '\
information_system_description: 'The emptiness isn''t a malfunction.\
\
  It''s information.\
\
  Your system is telling you something.\
\
  Not that you''re broken. Not that you''re failing. Not that something is permanently\
  wrong.\
\
  That something needs attention.\
\
  The emptiness is a signal. Not an error.\
\
  '\
uncertainty_presence_description: 'Uncertainty is present. That''s normal.\
\
  Not a malfunction. Not a problem to solve.\
\
  Just information.\
\
  '\
fixing_paradox_explanation: 'Every time you try to make the numbness go away, here''s\
  what actually happens:\
\
  You confirm it''s the enemy.\
\
  Your system thinks: If we''re fighting this, it must be a problem.\
\
  So it digs in deeper.\
\
  The solution became the problem.\
\
  '\
letting_it_be_description: 'You let it be there.\
\
  Not because you''re giving up. Not because you''ve surrendered.\
\
  Because it''s asking to be noticed, not fixed.\
\
  You acknowledge it. You stop fighting it.\
\
  Not because you''re resigned.\
\
  Because fighting it was never the answer.\
\
  '\
