\
  Same feeling. Different relationship.\
\
  '\
acting_while_state_example:\
  situation: 'Team meeting. Your manager asks for input on the project.\
\
    '\
  thought: 'I should contribute something, but I don''t care about any of this. Nothing\
    feels worth the effort of speaking. I''ll wait until I actually care about the\
    outcome.\
\
    '\
  action: 'You speak anyway. Your voice is flat. Your opinion is there. People respond\
    to it. The meeting continues.\
\
    You still don''t care.\
\
    That''s okay.\
\
    You moved anyway. Without the war.\
\
    '\
acting_alongside_detailed_example:\
  situation: Team meeting. Your manager asks for input on the project.\
  before: 'Say nothing. You don''t care enough to contribute. Then attack yourself\
    for not contributing. Then feel worse. Then care even less.\
\
    '\
  after: 'You speak anyway. Your voice is flat. Your opinion is there. People respond\
    to it. The meeting continues.\
\
    You still don''t care.\
\
    That''s okay.\
\
    You moved anyway. Without the war.\
\
    '\
core_shift_before: Nothing matters, so why bother.\
core_shift_after: I'm empty. And I'm doing it anyway.\
requirement_ending_description: 'The truce isn''t about feeling better.\
\
  It''s about stopping the second arrow.\
\
  The emptiness is the first arrow. The judgment is the second.\
\
  You can''t control the first arrow.\
\
  You can stop firing the second.\
\
  '\
feels_wrong_validation: 'This might feel wrong. Like you''re giving up.\
\
  You''re not giving up. You''re ending the war.\
\
  '\
calm_down_first_teaching: 'You''ve been taught your whole life: feel better first,\
  then act.\
\
  That''s a rule you made up. It''s a choice.\
\
  '\
rule_you_made_statement: 'That''s a rule you made up. It''s a choice.\
\
  '\
safety_caveats:\
  not_ignoring_danger: 'This doesn''t mean ignoring real danger. If something is actually\
    unsafe, don''t do it.\
\
    '\
  not_being_reckless: 'This doesn''t mean being reckless. It means acting while empty,\
    not acting without thinking.\
\
    '\
  danger_vs_discomfort: 'The difference: Discomfort isn''t danger. But the sentence\
    treats them the same.\
\
    Then: You avoided real danger\'97the pain of disappointment.\
\
    Now: You avoid discomfort\'97showing up while empty, being present while numb.\
\
    Discomfort isn''t danger. But the sentence treats them the same.\
\
    '\
new_relationship_framework:\
  notice: 'Notice the emptiness. Not to fight it. Just to see it.\
\
    '\
  assess: 'Assess: Does the emptiness mean I can''t do this.'\
  act: 'Act anyway. While empty. While numb. While the sentence is still running.\
\
    '\
what_you_gain_description: 'Your life back. The ability to move. The ability to show\
  up. The ability to engage.\
\
  '\
what_you_gain_examples:\
- You can respond while empty\
- You can speak up while numb\
- You can engage while feeling nothing\
- You can show up while the sentence is still running.\
sentence_was_never_problem_statement: 'The emptiness was never the problem. The waiting\
  was.\
\
  '\
permission_comes_from_you_statement: 'Permission comes from you. Not from the feeling.\
  Not from the emptiness. From you.\
\
  '\
that_version_is_enough_statement: 'The version of you sitting here right now\'97the one\
  who feels nothing, who can''t find the point\'97that version is enough.\
\
  '\
new_question: 'What can I do right now, even though I''m empty?\
\
  '\
theory_to_practice_bridge: 'You know the theory now: you don''t have to wait.\
\
  So how do you actually do it?\
\
  One small move at a time.\
\
  '\
small_move_definition: 'A small move is any action you take while the feeling is still\
  absent.\
\
  Not big. Not heroic. Not impressive.\
\
  Just: doing something anyway.\
\
  '\
small_move_examples:\
- context: Sending a text while empty\
  before: You tell yourself you'll send it when you care.\
  after: 'You notice the emptiness.\
\
    You send the text anyway.\
\
    It doesn''t have to be good. It doesn''t have to be meaningful. "Hey" is enough.\
\
    '\
- context: Responding to an email while numb\
  before: You tell yourself you'll respond when you care.\
  after: 'You notice the numbness.\
\
    You respond anyway.\
\
    Brief. Functional. Done.\
\
    '\
- context: Getting up while heavy\
  before: 'You wait. You tell yourself you''ll get up when you feel better.\
\
    '\
  after: 'You notice the weight.\
\
    You get up anyway.\
\
    Slow. Heavy. Up.\
\
    '\
small_moves_matter_explanation: 'These aren''t transformative. They''re not supposed\
  to be.\
\
  They''re evidence.\
\
  Evidence that you can move while not caring.\
\
  Evidence that action doesn''t require feeling.\
\
  Evidence that the sentence was wrong.\
\
  '\
repetition_learning_description: 'Your system learns through repetition.\
\
  Every time you move while empty, you''re teaching it:\
\
  We can do this even when feeling nothing.\
\
  Not that the emptiness goes away.\
\
  That you can move anyway.\
\
  '\
pattern_teaching_description: 'Every time you act while empty, you''re teaching your\
  system:\
\
  "We can do this even when feeling nothing."\
\
  Not that the feeling goes away.\
\
  That you can act anyway.\
\
  '\
old_pattern_description: 'Old pattern: Wait until you feel something. Then act.\
\
  The feeling never comes first. So you never act.\
\
  '\
new_pattern_description: 'New pattern: Notice the emptiness. Acknowledge it. Move\
  anyway.\
\
  The emptiness might still be there. But you moved.\
\
  '\
notice_instruction: Notice what you're feeling right now. Not to change it. Just to\
  see it.\
acknowledge_instruction: Acknowledge it. "I'm feeling empty right now." That's it.\
decide_instruction: 'Decide: keep going, or pause. Either is fine.'\
small_move_invitation: 'Pick one small thing you can do right now.\
\
  While feeling empty.\
\
  Do it.\
\
  Notice what happened.\
\
  '\
notice_without_fixing_framework:\
