  - Acknowledge it. "I'm feeling empty right now." That's it.\
  - Decide: keep going, or pause. Either is fine.\
  immediate_application: 'Do it now. [5-second pause]\
\
    Notice what happened.\
\
    '\
exercise_2_pranayama:\
  name: box_breath\
  intensity: L1\
  framing: 'This is a companion practice. Something to do while the feeling is there.\
\
    Not to make it go away. To be with it.\
\
    '\
  integration_bridge: 'Did the emptiness disappear?\
\
    Or did you discover you can breathe while it''s still there?\
\
    That''s what this proves: you can move while empty.\
\
    The emptiness might still be there. But you just did something anyway.\
\
    '\
what_youre_building_description: 'The ability to act while empty. The ability to move\
  while numb. The ability to show up while feeling nothing.\
\
  '\
assignment_prompt: 'Pick one small thing you can do right now.\
\
  While feeling empty.\
\
  Do it.\
\
  Notice what happened.\
\
  '\
what_changes_over_time_description: 'The relationship changes, not the state.\
\
  Not feeling better.\
\
  Moving anyway.\
\
  '\
from_wrong_to_normal_description: 'From feeling wrong to feeling normal.\
\
  Not because the emptiness left.\
\
  Because you stopped requiring it to.\
\
  '\
loud_description: 'Sometimes the emptiness isn''t quiet.\
\
  Sometimes it''s loud.\
\
  Body so heavy you can''t imagine standing. Mind so foggy you can''t hold a thought.\
  Everything so flat that even thinking about moving feels impossible.\
\
  '\
loud_vs_dangerous_distinction: 'And here''s what you need to know about volume:\
\
  Loud is not the same as impossible.\
\
  Everything feels flat when you open your eyes. Nothing seems worth doing when you\
  look at your day. Even people you care about feel distant, unreachable. The emptiness\
  sits in your chest like something permanent.\
\
  Heavy? Yes.\
\
  Impossible? No.\
\
  '\
loud_manifestations:\
- Body so heavy that getting out of bed feels like lifting weights underwater\
- Mind so numb that even simple thoughts feel like trudging through fog\
- Emotions so flat that nothing registers\'97not joy, not pain, not anything worth naming\
what_to_do_when_loud: 'Your system is signaling intensely. That doesn''t mean the\
  situation requires paralysis.\
\
  Body like concrete.\
\
  Mind like fog.\
\
  Emotions like they''re behind glass.\
\
  This is loud. This is not a verdict.\
\
  '\
exercise_1_extended_exhale:\
  name: extended_exhale\
  intensity: L2\
  parasympathetic_explanation: 'Extended exhale activates the parasympathetic nervous\
    system.\
\
    Not to make the emptiness go away. To breathe with it.\
\
    '\
  integration_bridge: 'Did the emptiness disappear?\
\
    Or did you discover you can breathe while it''s still there?\
\
    That''s what this proves: you can move while empty, even when it''s loud.\
\
    The emptiness might still be there. But you just breathed through it.\
\
    '\
