  name: feet_ground\
  intensity: L2\
  physical_anchoring_explanation: 'Grounding through your feet. Feeling the floor.\
    Not to make the emptiness go away. To be here with it.\
\
    '\
  integration_bridge: 'Did the emptiness disappear?\
\
    Or did you discover you can be grounded while it''s still there?\
\
    That''s what this proves: you can move while empty, even when it''s loud.\
\
    The emptiness might still be there. But you just grounded through it.\
\
    '\
acting_when_loud_scenario:\
  situation: 'Your manager asks you to lead a presentation next week.\
\
    '\
  physical_response: 'Body heavy. Mind flat. The request feels completely pointless.\
\
    '\
  notice_assess_act: 'Notice: I don''t care about this at all. Nothing in me wants\
    to do it.\
\
    Assess: Does that mean I can''t do it?\
\
    No.\
\
    Move: I''ll prepare anyway.\
\
    '\
volume_vs_danger_reframe: 'The emptiness can be at full volume while you still move\
  forward.\
\
  Volume is just volume. It doesn''t decide what you''re capable of.\
\
  '\
exercise_3_four_seven_eight:\
  name: four_seven_eight\
  intensity: L2\
  integration_bridge: 'Did the emptiness disappear?\
\
    Or did you discover you can breathe while it''s still there, even at full volume?\
\
    That''s what this proves: you can move while empty, even when it''s loud.\
\
    The emptiness might still be there. But you just breathed through it.\
\
    '\
volume_doesnt_dictate_description: 'Volume doesn''t determine actions.\
\
  The old question: How do I make myself care again?\
\
  The new question: Can I do this while caring about nothing?\
\
  '\
volume_matters_less_description: 'The more you move while it''s loud, the less the\
  volume matters.\
\
  Not because it gets quieter.\
\
  Because you stop requiring quiet.\
\
  '\
make_it_quieter_vs_act_while_loud: 'The real shift isn''t making it quieter.\
\
  It''s acting while it''s loud.\
\
  '\
something_shifted_description: 'You''re going to slip.\
\
  Not might. Not maybe. You''re going to slip.\
\
  And I need you to hear this clearly before it happens: that''s not failure. That''s\
  the shape of this.\
\
  '\
new_pattern_default_description: 'It''s been a decent stretch. Weeks, maybe. You''ve\
  been moving. Responding to things. Showing up while empty. The new pattern has been\
  working.\
\
  Then life does what life does.\
\
  '\
relationship_context:\
  before: 'You wait to respond. You wait to reach out.\
\
    People learn you don''t say yes. Invitations slow down.\
\
    '\
  after: 'You respond anyway. You reach out anyway.\
\
    People see you showing up. Invitations continue.\
\
    '\
  what_changes: 'The shift is subtle but profound: you stopped waiting to care before\
    connecting. You showed up while feeling nothing. And connection happened anyway.\
\
    '\
social_before: 'You wait to say yes. You wait to show up.\
\
  People learn you don''t engage.\
\
  '\
social_after: 'You say yes anyway. You show up anyway.\
\
  People see you engaging.\
\
  '\
social_context:\
  before: 'You wait to say yes. You wait to show up.\
\
    People learn you don''t engage.\
\
    '\
  after: 'You say yes anyway. You show up anyway.\
\
    People see you engaging.\
\
    '\
  what_you_notice: 'The emptiness doesn''t disappear. You just stop letting it decide\
    whether you show up.\
\
    '\
work_school_context:\
  before: 'You wait to speak up. You wait to share ideas.\
\
    Projects get assigned to others. Your competence stays invisible.\
\
    '\
  after: 'You speak up anyway. You share ideas anyway.\
\
    Projects include you. Your competence becomes visible.\
\
    '\
  speaking_up_becomes_normal: 'Professional growth doesn''t require motivation. It\
    requires showing up, consistently, while empty.\
\
    '\
