## Layer Stack Definition System\
\
The Layer Stack system controls which content layers are allowed in a book, preventing overstuffed chapters and tone incoherence.\
\
### Configuration Files\
\
- **
\f9\fs28 \cb11 config/layer_stack.yaml
\f0\fs32 \cb7 **: Book-level layer configuration\
- **
\f9\fs28 \cb11 config/template_profile.yaml
\f0\fs32 \cb7 **: Template defaults\
- **
\f9\fs28 \cb11 config/chapter_role_map.yaml
\f0\fs32 \cb7 **: Chapter role assignments\
- **
\f9\fs28 \cb11 config/exercise_policy.yaml
\f0\fs32 \cb7 **: Exercise controls\
- **
\f9\fs28 \cb11 config/editorial_freeze.yaml
\f0\fs32 \cb7 **: Protected sections\
\
### Usage\
\
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0

\f9 \cf0 bash\
# Validate book against layer stack\
python3 -m phoenix_protocol.cli validate-layers \\\
  --book qa_gen_z_depression_READY_FOR_QA.md \\\
  --output layer_stack_validation_report.md
\f0 \
\
### Layers Controlled\
\
- **Narrative**: Story, vignette, lived experience\
- **Concept**: Explanation, framing, insight\
- **Exercise**: Somatic / meditative instruction\
- **Reflection**: Prompts, journaling, integration\
- **Editorial Freeze**: Protected text that cannot be regenerated\cb1 \
